  <title>Change your user picture</title>
  <steps>
   <item>
   <p>
      Press <keyseq><key> Alt </key><key> F1 </key></keyseq> to go to the <gui> Activities </gui> overview.
   </p>
   </item>
   <item>
   <p>
     Type 'about me' in the <gui> Type to search </gui> textbox. Click on the <gui> About me </gui> icon under Preferences, when it appears.
   </p>
   </item>
   <item>
   <p>
   Click on the picture square to the left of the username. You can select from the many pictures available from the /usr/share/pixmaps/faces directory.
   </p>
   </item>
      <item>
   <p>
   You can also select a picture from a different folder on your computer by clicking on a folder of choice from the <gui> Places </gui> menu on the left.
   </p>
   </item>
   <item>
   <p>
  Select the picture by clicking on the name of the file and then clicking <gui> Open </gui>.  The picture has been applied.
   </p>
   </item>
   <item>
   <p>
   Click <gui> Close </gui>.
   </p>
   </item>
  </steps>

